                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51 Salt Funds/105: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="#p_JNT1" type="from"
                            >Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-04-19T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >April 19, 1932—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received April 19—3 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>445. The Minister’s April 4, 10 a.m. Following from American Consul General at
                    Mukden: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“April 18, 4 p.m. Reliably informed that the offices of the district
                            inspector after closing of Salt Administration at Newchang were
                            definitely closed on April 15th by the Japanese adviser of the Salt
                            Transportation Office, the staff having been ejected and the offices
                            sealed.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>For the Minister:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
